Ray Sinclair plays Dwayne Miller and Cory Robinson plays Baker
Wrestling fans film fans you will not be disappointed with SLEEPER

I saw this movie in Australia a couple years ago at a film festival. From what I remember it had action and suspense. An obsessed maniac seeks out this chick and kills anyone that stands in his way. Her friends try to protect her from the carnage, but soon stuff happens (not spoiling things). The two detectives assigned to find and retrieve the killer have only that night to capture him and make sure he doesn't harm or kidnap the girl. The ending I remember had a twist I never saw coming, which makes the film worth watching till the end. It's a great story and recommend it. Plus it's an Aussie film with an American wrestler, what more to like.
Such brutality, but with a twist.

The acting wasn't that great, but it was a low budget film. There were also some unbelievable moments when showing the stupidity of the police, but I have seen much worse. What sets this movie apart is that the story was good and there was an excellent twist to the ending. Based on that I gave it a four. You may not like it, but if you look below the low budget pitfalls; you will see the work of a very talented writer showing through.
